<td class="mbox-image">
<div style="width: 52px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Ambox_content.png" class="image" title="Ambox content.png"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png" width="40" height="40" border="0" /></a></div>
</td>
<td class="mbox-text" style="">This article <b>describes a work or element of fiction in a primarily <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(writing_about_fiction)" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style (writing about fiction)">in-universe</a> style</b>. Please <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rules_of_Acquisition&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rules_of_Acquisition&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow">help rewrite it</a> to <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(writing_about_fiction)" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style (writing about fiction)">explain the fiction more clearly and provide non-fictional perspective</a>.</td>
</tr>
